#30335
Wall~
Looking down from the heights of the wall you look out over the docks
of the city. Large warehouses hold produce been brought into or been
shipped out of the city. Traders and merchants haggle trying to get
the best - or cheapest, depending on which side they are on - price for
their goods. Sailors lustfully wander along the low class waterfront
dives, soaking up alcohol as fast as possible before they have to sail
out again to sea.
