#30492
Mess hall~
Built into the walls of the city, the mess hall is spartan. Every three 
days, the watch changes and there is nothing to say soldiers will serve 
at the same place along the wall again soon. A rough wooden bench and 
table are jammed into the room, with barely room to sit without been 
squashed against the walls. Two small doors, iron banded and with heavy 
locks lead out to the stairs up to the wall top and to the stores for 
this part of the wall.
